# Seqera-aligned guidance without the Seqera CLI

## Do not call `seqera` from the agent

Do **not** run **`seqera ai`** or other **`seqera`** commands unless the user explicitly asks and confirms the CLI is installed. Prefer **this rule** plus **`.agents/skills/seqera/SKILL.md`** and official URLs below.

## Where the “Seqera skills” live

- **Project skill (portable):** `.agents/skills/seqera/SKILL.md` — bwa-neo facts, Pixi+Nextflow benchmark layout, publication manifest.
- **Seqera’s discovery spec:** [Skills](https://docs.seqera.io/platform-cloud/seqera-ai/skills) (directory precedence, 5 KB hint).

## How to help

- Nextflow DSL2, nf-core patterns, Seqera Platform: use current best practices and **https://docs.seqera.io/** (including [Seqera AI overview](https://docs.seqera.io/platform-cloud/seqera-ai/) for product concepts, not for mandatory CLI use).
- **Benchmarks in this repo:** `benchmarks/at_scale/README.md` — run with **`pixi run bench`** or **`pixi run bench-neo-only`** from `benchmarks/at_scale/` (dependencies and Nextflow are defined in **`pixi.toml`**; do not use a Makefile there).

## bwa-neo code and tests

Use `AGENTS.md`, `design.md`, `requirements.md`, and `tasks.md` for build scope outside the Pixi benchmark environment.
